# AIGX Context

This repository uses AIGX (AI Genome Exchange) — a per-file context format for AI coding agents. The genome lives in `.aigx/`.

## Read protocol

For every file you will edit:
1. Find its `<file path="...">` entry in `.aigx/files.aigx`
2. Read its `<role>` — what the file does
3. Obey `<forbid pri="CRIT">` — hard constraint, never violate
4. Heed `<gotcha>` — the single worst pitfall here
5. Verify every `<check>` id before finishing

Full protocol in `.aigx/protocol.aigx`.

## Keeping the genome current

From `.aigx/agent.aigx`:
- Rename a file → update `path` in `files.aigx`, same change-set
- Create a new file → add a `<file>` entry in `files.aigx`
- Never rename rule ids — only update their text in-place

## Validate

```bash
python tools/aigx-lint/aigx_lint.py --root .
```
